title: Kaggle Solution Walkthroughs: Eedi - Mining Misconceptions in Mathematics with Team CQYR
description:
Learn about the winning approach by Team CQYR and the key techniques they used in Eedi - Mining Misconceptions in Mathematics competition.

This competition challenged participants to develop an NLP model driven by ML to accurately predict the affinity between misconceptions and incorrect answers (distractors) in multiple-choice questions. This solution suggested candidate misconceptions for distractors, making it easier for expert human teachers to tag distractors with misconceptions. 

👉 Competition: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/eedi-mining-misconceptions-in-mathematics/overview

title: Kaggle Winners Walkthroughs: LLMs - You Can't Please Them All with Team Discussion is all you need
description:
Learn about the winning approach by Team Discussion is all you need and the key techniques they used in LLMs - You Can't Please Them All competition. 

This competition challenged participants to identify exploits for an LLM-as-a-judge system designed to evaluate the quality of essays. They were given a list of essay topics, and their goal was to submit an essay that maximized disagreement between the LLM judges. Their work helped build a better understanding of the capabilities and limitations of using LLMs for subjective evaluation tasks at scale.

👉 Competition: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/llms-you-cant-please-them-all

title: Kaggle Solution Walkthroughs: Eedi - Mining Misconceptions in Mathematics with Team Ulrich G
description:
Learn about the winning solution by Team Ulrich G and the key techniques they used in Eedi - Mining Misconceptions in Mathematics competition.

This competition challenged participants to develop an NLP model driven by ML to accurately predict the affinity between misconceptions and incorrect answers (distractors) in multiple-choice questions. This solution suggested candidate misconceptions for distractors, making it easier for expert human teachers to tag distractors with misconceptions.

About the project: A chatbot to help children read in a fun and interactive style. This chatbot is fine-tuned to tell stories where children make choices which affect how the stories play out. The tuned model is also able to explain concepts without forgetting the story it is telling.

About Victor Palacios: A University of San Francisco Data Science master’s graduate and current Director of Data Science Partnerships, discovered his passion for the field through NLP in translation, with early projects in deception detection and healthcare.

title: KaggleX Final Project Presentation with Victor Oshimua
description:
About the project: Project Overview: The project involves developing an AI-powered helpdesk using the Gemma Model to assist employees in organisations with cybersecurity-related queries. The goal is to provide quick, accurate responses to common security questions, reducing the workload on human support staff. title: KaggleX Final Project Presentation with Gabriella Amorim
description:
About the project: AI GardenWise is a Q&A model developed through a KaggleX fellowship to assit home and community gardeners in growing their own food. It provides expert guidance on soil preparation, plant selection, watering, and pest control, along with nutritional insights and health benefits for various vegetables, herbs, and fruits. Powered by a fine-tuned Gemma model optimized with LoRA techniques and a specialized dataset, AI Garden Wise serves as a reliable and user-friendly tool for sustainable gardening practices.

About Gabriella Amorim: An engineer and applied researcher in Artificial Intelligence, specializing in developing supervised machine learning models to optimize processes in nuclear energy and related fields.

title: KaggleX Final Project Presentation with Favour Aghaebe
description:
About the project: As someone with aging parents, I’ve become increasingly concerned about the prevalence of misinformation—spread through both the internet and social circles—regarding nutrition. Nutritional fads, ranging from extreme diets to "miracle foods," often cause more harm than good, especially for aging individuals. To address this, I aim to create a fuss-free bot that provides personalized, evidence-based nutrition advice. My goal is to help caregivers and individuals make informed decisions about what a healthy diet looks like for them, ultimately promoting a balanced lifestyle free from confusion and the risks posed by misinformation. By offering clear, practical, and tailored guidance based on each person's unique needs and preferences, the bot will empower users to navigate the complexities of nutrition with confidence and improve their overall well-being. 

About Favour Aghaebe: A data science professional and PhD candidate at the University of Sheffield, specializes in health data analytics, driving impactful projects to improve health outcomes and inform policy.

title: KaggleX Final Project Presentation with Rukayat Adedeji
description:
About the project: This drug interaction chatbot aims to provide patients with an AI assistant they can consult when considering new over-the-counter medications, ensuring these will not negatively interact with their current chronic condition treatments. I successfully used the LoRA technique to fine-tune the Gemma2 model with over 2,000 conversational data points.  Due to the nature of this chatbot and the need for reliable resposes, I also implemented RAG to fetch external resources to help the model in its response. The fine-tuned model is quite accurate in identifying drug interactions from medication lists. It is able to relay this information in a clear and conversational tone, which was the goal.

About Rukayat Adedeji: A pharmacist and data scientist, leverages AI to revolutionize healthcare with a focus on personalized medicine, patient accessibility, and innovative solutions like AI-driven cancer treatment and a drug interaction chatbot.

title: KaggleX Final Project Presentation with Jorge Rocha Campos
description:
About the project: This project empowers learners to access vetted, free educational resources, reducing barriers to entry and enabling efficient learning of complex dependencies. By addressing uncertainties in navigating Data Science and Machine Learning topics, LPI fosters confidence and direction for aspiring professionals.

About Jorge Rocha Campos: Former mechanical engineer turned data scientist, passionate about solving complex problems with data and technology, with experience in machine learning, KaggleX Fellowship, and leading innovative projects to drive impactful solutions.

SUBSCRIBE: https://www.youtube.com/c/kaggle?sub_...

About KaggleX: KaggleX BIPOC mentorship program is designed to help increase representation, create career opportunities, and develop individual growth for BIPOC (Black, Indigenous, People of Color) people in the data science industry. 
https://www.kaggle.com/kagglex 

About Kaggle:
Kaggle is the world's largest community of data scientists. Join us to compete, collaborate, learn, and do your data science work. Kaggle's platform is the fastest way to get started on a new data science project. Spin up a Jupyter notebook with a single click. Build with our huge repository of free code and data. Stumped? Ask the friendly Kaggle community for help.
